Priests are divine healers who split from the Cleric tradition during the Hour of Quiet Thunder schism.
They withdrew from administrative work and combat theology to devote entirely to restoration, consecration, and healing.
Combat role is dedicated healer and ward-keeper with the most sophisticated healing methodology of any tradition.
Key abilities include sustained miracle-channel operation, compound condition treatment, and ward-network maintenance.
The great ward-networks are their signature achievement: consecrated shelter systems protecting against undead and corruption.
Ward maintenance requires constant renewal of seals, inspection of anchors, and community relationship management.
A Priest sustaining a healing channel is substantially less able to defend themselves.
Priests work in partnership with Paladins: Paladins create secure ground, Priests sustain healing within it.
The Templar class synthesizes Priest restoration with Paladin advance doctrine into a single practitioner.
Direct service to suffering is held as the ultimate expression of divine power, not a lesser application.
